# MEMORY.md (template)

> The top-level index of your memory directory. Loaded into Claude's context every conversation. Each entry is one line: title + filename + one-line hook.

## How to use this file

- One-line pointers only — content lives in the linked files
- Group by topic, not chronologically
- Keep under 200 lines (entries beyond that get truncated in context loading)
- Updated automatically by `/memory-curator` on each audit

